1
00:00:56,303 --> 00:00:58,973
FILING FOR LOVE

2
00:01:06,855 --> 00:01:08,148
Hello, everyone.

3
00:01:08,774 --> 00:01:12,361
I'm Park A-jeong, VP Jeon Jae-yeol's
former executive assistant.

4
00:01:15,281 --> 00:01:17,283
Your secretary? What on earth...

5
00:01:17,366 --> 00:01:18,534
What is all this?

6
00:01:19,910 --> 00:01:21,245
What trick are you pulling again?

7
00:01:21,328 --> 00:01:22,746
It's not a trick, Father.

8
00:01:22,830 --> 00:01:25,916
She made the brave call
to take a stand for our company.

9
00:01:26,375 --> 00:01:29,295
Are all Haemu shareholder meetings
this haphazard and unplanned?

10
00:01:30,296 --> 00:01:32,298
Do you allow just anyone
to stand and speak?

11
00:01:32,381 --> 00:01:36,093
I'm here because the shareholders
have a right to know.

12
00:01:36,635 --> 00:01:40,347
Only shareholders
are allowed to speak at...

13
00:01:47,980 --> 00:01:51,900
According to the report
I'm holding in my hand

14
00:01:52,234 --> 00:01:55,571
when VP Jeon Jae-yeol
was CEO of Haemu Pharmaceutical

15
00:01:55,654 --> 00:01:57,615
he transferred billions of won
without authorization

16
00:01:57,698 --> 00:02:00,075
to the medical foundation
he established.

17
00:02:00,367 --> 00:02:03,162
However, no audit was carried out.
Actually...

18
00:02:03,245 --> 00:02:04,955
it was practically impossible.

19
00:02:05,289 --> 00:02:06,457
That's because

20
00:02:06,540 --> 00:02:10,252
Joo In-a, the Head of Audit,
who was responsible for investigating

21
00:02:10,753 --> 00:02:12,713
covered up the transfers.

22
00:02:18,802 --> 00:02:21,221
Do you admit to it, Ms. Joo?

23
00:02:38,030 --> 00:02:41,241
It's true that Haemu Pharmaceutical
donated to Jei Medical Foundation.

24
00:02:42,868 --> 00:02:46,789
But I concluded there were
no issues with legal proceedings.

25
00:02:46,872 --> 00:02:48,749
Just because you conclude
that there are no issues

26
00:02:48,832 --> 00:02:50,542
does that mean
you don't have to conduct an audit?

27
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:53,712
Auditing is about risk management.

28
00:02:54,296 --> 00:02:56,674
I judged that the risk
of conducting the audit

29
00:02:56,924 --> 00:02:59,927
was greater than the risk
of not conducting it.

30
00:03:00,010 --> 00:03:01,679
OH HYUN-YOUNG
JEON JAE-YEOL

31
00:03:02,680 --> 00:03:05,849
Political and cliquish factions exist
within Haemu regarding succession.

32
00:03:06,725 --> 00:03:10,646
I thought the investigation
would become politically charged

33
00:03:10,729 --> 00:03:13,565
putting Haemu
into even worse turmoil.

34
00:03:13,649 --> 00:03:15,693
My point is

35
00:03:16,110 --> 00:03:18,779
who gives you
the right to decide that?

36
00:03:18,862 --> 00:03:20,948
It's my job to make such decisions.

37
00:03:21,198 --> 00:03:24,034
How can we trust Ms. Joo's decision?

38
00:03:24,368 --> 00:03:27,079
VP Jeon Jae-yeol
and Head of Audit Joo In-a

39
00:03:27,162 --> 00:03:28,497
were in a romantic relationship.

40
00:03:29,581 --> 00:03:33,627
Was Ms. Joo's decision based
solely on the company's interests?

41
00:03:34,086 --> 00:03:35,754
What if she made that choice

42
00:03:36,338 --> 00:03:38,006
for VP Jeon Jae-yeol's sake?

43
00:03:41,593 --> 00:03:44,012
Goodness, what on earth
is all this about?

44
00:03:46,348 --> 00:03:47,683
Why didn't you do anything?

45
00:03:48,851 --> 00:03:51,270
What were you doing while the company
ended up in this state?

46
00:03:52,938 --> 00:03:53,939
- Father.
- Sir.

47
00:03:54,106 --> 00:03:55,190
- Father.
- Father.

48
00:03:55,274 --> 00:03:56,358
Are you all right?

49
00:03:56,608 --> 00:03:57,860
- Oh, no.
- Father!

50
00:03:57,943 --> 00:03:59,862
At the Haemu Group
shareholder meeting held today

51
00:03:59,945 --> 00:04:02,197
allegations surfaced
that the Head of Audit covered up

52
00:04:02,281 --> 00:04:05,325
VP Jeon Jae-yeol's misconduct,
sparking major controversy.

53
00:04:06,034 --> 00:04:10,622
Haemu Group President Jeon Moo-tae
collapsed during the meeting

54
00:04:10,706 --> 00:04:12,583
which was immediately suspended.

55
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:15,210
Haemu Group convened
an emergency board meeting

56
00:04:15,294 --> 00:04:18,255
to launch a wide-scale investigation
into the allegations.

57
00:04:18,797 --> 00:04:21,884
With concerns
over both the chairman's health

58
00:04:21,967 --> 00:04:25,137
and management ethics intensifying

59
00:04:25,220 --> 00:04:29,433
Haemu Group's succession battle
has again fallen into turmoil.

60
00:04:42,446 --> 00:04:44,907
Gosh, with the company in this mess

61
00:04:45,240 --> 00:04:47,326
I could barely swallow my food.

62
00:04:47,409 --> 00:04:49,077
You emptied your bowl today.

63
00:04:49,328 --> 00:04:50,704
Goodness gracious.

64
00:04:50,788 --> 00:04:53,582
I heard the basement press room
filled up after the news came out.

65
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:57,127
It looks like
all the journalists are here.

66
00:04:58,045 --> 00:05:01,423
I think it's drawing more attention
because of the VP's scandal.

67
00:05:01,882 --> 00:05:04,218
Ms. Joo's personal information is
already all over the internet.

68
00:05:04,426 --> 00:05:06,553
Oh, gosh. Guys.

69
00:05:06,637 --> 00:05:08,889
Let's watch what we say in public.

70
00:05:08,972 --> 00:05:12,226
If your wife or boyfriend asks,
just say you don't know anything.

71
00:05:12,309 --> 00:05:13,852
- We never know how it'll spread.
- Okay.

72
00:05:13,936 --> 00:05:15,771
It's true
we don't really know anything.

73
00:05:16,980 --> 00:05:19,149
About Ms. Park's report...

74
00:05:19,233 --> 00:05:20,692
How much of it do you think is true?

75
00:05:21,026 --> 00:05:23,821
If someone like Ms. Joo covered it up

76
00:05:23,904 --> 00:05:27,491
don't you think there's still
something between her and the VP?

77
00:05:28,659 --> 00:05:29,910
There isn't.

78
00:05:31,078 --> 00:05:33,372
How do you know that, Ms. Yoon?

79
00:05:33,997 --> 00:05:36,500
I know who Ms. Joo is dating now.

80
00:05:36,667 --> 00:05:38,961
- What?
- It's not our VP.

81
00:05:40,170 --> 00:05:41,839
- Who is it?
- Who is it?

82
00:05:43,757 --> 00:05:46,677
It's someone we all know.

83
00:05:46,760 --> 00:05:48,595
- Someone we know? Who?
- I don't know anyone.

84
00:05:48,679 --> 00:05:49,847
- What?
- Who is it?

85
00:05:50,138 --> 00:05:51,390
- Who is it?
- Who is it?

86
00:05:51,473 --> 00:05:53,433
- Who is it?
- Yes, who is it? Tell us.

87
00:05:53,517 --> 00:05:55,477
- Take a look around.
- What?

88
00:05:55,853 --> 00:05:57,271
- Come on.
- You can't just walk off.

89
00:05:57,354 --> 00:05:59,273
- You need to tell us.
- What do you know?

90
00:05:59,356 --> 00:06:00,482
- Tell me.
- Talk to us.

91
00:06:09,825 --> 00:06:11,285
HEAD OF AUDIT

92
00:06:15,163 --> 00:06:17,291
They've been keeping her all day.

93
00:06:21,461 --> 00:06:24,464
SPECIAL INVESTIGATION COMMITTEE

94
00:06:24,923 --> 00:06:26,425
State your relationship with VP Jeon

95
00:06:26,508 --> 00:06:28,510
when you reviewed
the Jei Medical Foundation case.

96
00:06:29,011 --> 00:06:30,554
We weren't in any relationship.

97
00:06:30,762 --> 00:06:32,097
You two used to date.

98
00:06:32,180 --> 00:06:33,307
We weren't at the time.

99
00:06:33,390 --> 00:06:35,851
No one who was a couple
goes back to being just strangers.

100
00:06:35,934 --> 00:06:38,896
Could there be any worse relationship
than a couple who broke up?

101
00:06:39,897 --> 00:06:41,315
It's worse off than strangers.

102
00:06:42,149 --> 00:06:44,735
VP Jeon said
he still had feelings for you.

103
00:06:44,818 --> 00:06:45,819
I did not.

104
00:06:45,903 --> 00:06:48,572
Even when you were reviewing
the medical foundation case?

105
00:06:50,490 --> 00:06:51,783
Even then.

106
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:54,328
Here are Jei Medical Foundation's
shareholding records

107
00:06:54,411 --> 00:06:57,372
meeting minutes of decision-making
processes at Haemu Pharmaceutical

108
00:06:57,456 --> 00:07:00,417
sponsorship approvals,
and fund usage records.

109
00:07:01,168 --> 00:07:03,086
You'll see for yourself
if you read those.

110
00:07:03,754 --> 00:07:06,089
As CEO at the time, I played no part
in running the foundation

111
00:07:06,590 --> 00:07:10,010
nor influenced Haemu Pharmaceutical's
decision-making process.

112
00:07:10,344 --> 00:07:12,679
All funds were used appropriately

113
00:07:12,763 --> 00:07:13,805
within their means.

114
00:07:14,514 --> 00:07:17,017
If there were no issues
in the process

115
00:07:17,309 --> 00:07:20,103
then there was no fault
on Ms. Joo's part to decide

116
00:07:20,562 --> 00:07:21,939
not to investigate.

117
00:07:22,397 --> 00:07:26,318
Whether she was at fault or not
will be decided in court.

118
00:07:26,568 --> 00:07:28,654
There clearly are
grounds for an argument.

119
00:07:28,737 --> 00:07:31,573
I think we should find out
exactly why she didn't look into it.

120
00:07:32,741 --> 00:07:33,951
Don't you think?

121
00:07:49,841 --> 00:07:52,552
It'll be more complicated
than we thought.

122
00:07:54,596 --> 00:07:55,722
What did Joo In-a say?

123
00:07:56,139 --> 00:07:58,976
She's maintaining
that she made an official call.

124
00:08:00,644 --> 00:08:03,230
Why is she still fighting
when we've come this far?

125
00:08:05,440 --> 00:08:06,817
Whether Jae-yeol's guilty or not

126
00:08:06,900 --> 00:08:09,319
won't matter
once news of the scandal gets out.

127
00:08:09,403 --> 00:08:11,113
Bring Joo In-a down at all costs.

128
00:08:11,196 --> 00:08:12,906
- Yes, sir.
- Okay.

129
00:08:24,084 --> 00:08:26,169
I'm with Haesin Daily. Can we talk?

130
00:08:26,253 --> 00:08:27,713
Hello, this is XTM.

131
00:08:27,796 --> 00:08:29,047
Are you available for an interview?

132
00:08:29,131 --> 00:08:30,757
The VP's mistress

133
00:08:30,841 --> 00:08:33,010
- should rot in a pit forever.
- Gosh, it's gross.

134
00:08:33,635 --> 00:08:35,095
Hello, Ms. Joo.

135
00:08:36,680 --> 00:08:37,723
Gosh.

136
00:08:38,432 --> 00:08:39,850
You are a beauty.

137
00:08:41,309 --> 00:08:44,771
Oh, I'm Park Dae-geun
with Daily Hansung.

138
00:08:45,397 --> 00:08:47,482
I have nothing to say. Sorry.

139
00:08:48,150 --> 00:08:50,902
You grew up in Mipo, didn't you?

140
00:08:52,612 --> 00:08:54,406
You were
quite a popular figure there, too.

141
00:08:55,532 --> 00:08:57,325
I heard the smart, pretty girl

142
00:08:57,784 --> 00:09:00,245
grew up in a messed-up family.

143
00:09:08,295 --> 00:09:09,504
Daily Hansung?

144
00:09:10,380 --> 00:09:12,632
You probably didn't know because
you work for a media-like outlet

145
00:09:12,716 --> 00:09:14,384
that just copies social media posts

146
00:09:15,010 --> 00:09:17,387
and writes clickbait articles
without doing real reporting.

147
00:09:17,846 --> 00:09:19,556
This area is restricted to reporters.

148
00:09:20,724 --> 00:09:21,725
Security?

149
00:09:22,309 --> 00:09:23,852
An outsider got in.

150
00:09:27,939 --> 00:09:29,983
- I need you to leave.
- Sorry.

151
00:09:30,484 --> 00:09:31,526
My bad.

152
00:09:50,712 --> 00:09:51,713
Hop in.

153
00:10:04,267 --> 00:10:06,394
Wow, didn't that just feel
like we were filming an action movie?

154
00:10:07,104 --> 00:10:08,688
I'd call it a romance,
not an action film

155
00:10:08,772 --> 00:10:10,232
because I appeared
at just the right moment.

156
00:10:10,649 --> 00:10:12,234
Let's call it a romantic action film.

157
00:10:15,153 --> 00:10:16,696
How do you feel?

158
00:10:16,780 --> 00:10:18,406
It must be hard
being questioned all day long.

159
00:10:18,490 --> 00:10:19,866
It was nothing.

160
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:22,661
I was a nude model for a long time.

161
00:10:22,744 --> 00:10:23,870
It was not tough one bit.

162
00:10:33,630 --> 00:10:35,173
She said she wasn't tired one bit.

163
00:10:45,058 --> 00:10:46,643
Oh, gosh. I dozed off.

164
00:10:49,479 --> 00:10:51,064
I didn't snore, did I?

165
00:10:52,232 --> 00:10:53,567
You did, actually.

166
00:10:57,737 --> 00:10:58,905
Did I really?

167
00:10:59,489 --> 00:11:00,907
Did I snore?

168
00:11:00,991 --> 00:11:02,868
You're lying, aren't you?

169
00:11:04,953 --> 00:11:06,496
Are you serious?

170
00:11:06,580 --> 00:11:08,081
Did I really snore?

171
00:11:08,165 --> 00:11:10,292
Really? Honestly?
No, I didn't, did I?

172
00:11:10,375 --> 00:11:12,919
Was I really snoring? Seriously?

173
00:11:13,003 --> 00:11:14,171
- Did I...
- You didn't.

174
00:11:14,588 --> 00:11:16,339
You didn't snore. It was a joke.

175
00:11:18,675 --> 00:11:20,927
But you were dead asleep, though.

176
00:11:21,303 --> 00:11:23,305
As soon as you get home

177
00:11:23,388 --> 00:11:25,557
take a shower
then jump right into bed.

178
00:11:26,933 --> 00:11:28,310
You nag too much.

179
00:11:29,019 --> 00:11:30,103
I'll do that.

180
00:11:33,106 --> 00:11:34,441
Drop me off over there.

181
00:11:43,116 --> 00:11:44,367
Thanks for the ride.

182
00:11:44,451 --> 00:11:46,077
Don't get out. Go on home.

183
00:11:46,161 --> 00:11:47,412
No, I'll walk you home first.

184
00:11:47,704 --> 00:11:50,415
You dropped me off.
Now let me see you drive off.

185
00:11:50,498 --> 00:11:52,042
I'll leave
after I see you get inside.

186
00:11:52,959 --> 00:11:54,419
I want to see you off.

187
00:11:55,754 --> 00:11:57,839
Let's do this, then. We'll wave.

188
00:11:58,298 --> 00:12:00,133
Bye. Take care.

189
00:12:01,092 --> 00:12:02,219
Aren't I good at walking backward?

190
00:12:08,558 --> 00:12:10,060
There are reporters
outside your building.

191
00:12:46,888 --> 00:12:47,931
It's freezing cold.

192
00:13:13,039 --> 00:13:14,916
I'll send you some photos.

193
00:13:15,458 --> 00:13:16,793
Look into someone for me.

194
00:13:18,461 --> 00:13:21,881
- If you're done, come out and eat.
- Okay.

195
00:13:27,387 --> 00:13:29,681
It's a bit big, but it works.
How do I look?

196
00:13:30,849 --> 00:13:33,018
It's not too big at all.
You look pretty.

197
00:13:36,855 --> 00:13:40,191
My gosh. What is all this?
It's a total feast.

198
00:13:40,275 --> 00:13:42,068
My sisters came by last weekend.

199
00:13:42,485 --> 00:13:45,864
They made kimchi, so I asked for some
to share with you.

200
00:13:46,072 --> 00:13:48,783
They brought enough food
to fill a whole fridge.

201
00:13:48,867 --> 00:13:51,411
Do people make seasoned cockles
when making kimchi?

202
00:13:52,495 --> 00:13:55,206
No, they brought this
because it's my favorite.

203
00:13:55,498 --> 00:13:57,208
Cockles are hard to clean

204
00:13:57,292 --> 00:13:59,878
so I tell my mom to stop making them,
but she still does it.

205
00:14:00,337 --> 00:14:01,755
She could've made just a little.

206
00:14:02,005 --> 00:14:04,466
She makes way too much,
and I can never eat it all.

207
00:14:06,217 --> 00:14:07,218
Noh Ki-jun.

208
00:14:07,844 --> 00:14:10,096
Your family adores you.

209
00:14:11,222 --> 00:14:12,474
Too much for my liking.

210
00:14:12,557 --> 00:14:14,768
Too much love is a nuisance, too.

211
00:14:16,978 --> 00:14:18,188
What a spoiled thing to say.

212
00:14:21,399 --> 00:14:22,692
Thanks for the food.

213
00:14:23,818 --> 00:14:25,528
What are your sisters like?

214
00:14:25,612 --> 00:14:27,238
I want to hear about them.

215
00:14:30,325 --> 00:14:31,368
My older sisters...

216
00:14:34,245 --> 00:14:36,122
- They're just sisters.
- What?

217
00:14:36,206 --> 00:14:37,499
There's not much to say.

218
00:14:38,666 --> 00:14:39,667
- Oh, wait.
- What?

219
00:14:40,460 --> 00:14:43,880
- My sisters' kids are adorable.
- Let me see.

220
00:14:45,757 --> 00:14:46,758
Here.

221
00:14:47,926 --> 00:14:49,094
That's so cute.

222
00:14:56,101 --> 00:14:57,727
How sweet...

223
00:15:19,874 --> 00:15:21,835
HAEMU'S BROTHERLY STRIFE:
FEMME FATALE AUDITOR AT THE CENTER

224
00:15:32,470 --> 00:15:34,305
Guys, did you all read...

225
00:15:38,977 --> 00:15:40,103
You're reading it.

226
00:15:47,193 --> 00:15:50,947
The Head of Audit is accused
of an affair with VP Jeon Jae-yeol.

227
00:15:51,781 --> 00:15:53,658
Does infidelity run in her family?

228
00:15:54,659 --> 00:15:58,663
It's worth noting Joo was born
from an extramarital affair.

229
00:15:59,539 --> 00:16:02,292
But the string of men surrounding her
who shook an entire corporation

230
00:16:02,375 --> 00:16:03,835
doesn't end here.

231
00:16:04,627 --> 00:16:05,712
According to my research...

232
00:16:05,795 --> 00:16:08,673
"It has been confirmed
that she is dating Noh

233
00:16:08,756 --> 00:16:11,468
one of her subordinates
in the Audit Team."

234
00:16:12,135 --> 00:16:15,221
What's even more shocking is that
Noh was in charge of investigating

235
00:16:15,305 --> 00:16:16,598
the Haemu Pharmaceutical case

236
00:16:17,474 --> 00:16:20,768
that's at the center
of the controversy."

237
00:16:25,106 --> 00:16:27,775
We could get something
if we piece this together nicely.

238
00:16:28,568 --> 00:16:32,071
I was getting annoyed
at how things were dragging on.

239
00:16:48,129 --> 00:16:49,130
HAEMU'S BROTHERLY STRIFE

240
00:16:49,214 --> 00:16:50,215
Mr. Noh.

241
00:16:51,424 --> 00:16:54,385
Is this article about you?
That you're her lover?

242
00:16:56,429 --> 00:16:58,973
What's this about Ms. Joo
being born out of wedlock?

243
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:02,227
The reporter went way over the line.

244
00:17:04,562 --> 00:17:06,981
Mr. Noh, where are you going?

245
00:17:17,575 --> 00:17:19,285
I swear, it's the truth.

246
00:17:19,369 --> 00:17:20,370
- No way.
- No way.

247
00:17:20,453 --> 00:17:22,580
Come on. I confirmed it.

248
00:17:22,664 --> 00:17:23,665
Are you sure?

249
00:17:24,749 --> 00:17:27,794
The two went
into Noh's place at night.

250
00:17:28,878 --> 00:17:30,296
She was there for a long time.

251
00:17:30,380 --> 00:17:32,006
That's a scoop.

252
00:17:32,090 --> 00:17:34,551
- What?
- Was she really born out of wedlock?

253
00:17:34,634 --> 00:17:36,469
A friend of mine is from Mipo.

254
00:17:36,553 --> 00:17:38,846
The mother and daughter duo
were social outcasts.

255
00:17:38,930 --> 00:17:39,973
Oh, dear...

256
00:17:40,890 --> 00:17:43,685
"The poor Head of Audit
who followed in her parents' steps."

257
00:17:44,727 --> 00:17:46,020
Isn't that hilarious?

258
00:17:46,104 --> 00:17:47,564
You could turn it into a movie.

259
00:17:50,275 --> 00:17:51,651
Watch what you say.

260
00:17:53,319 --> 00:17:54,320
Oh, my gosh.

261
00:17:55,822 --> 00:17:57,991
- This is Mr. Noh Ki-jun.
- I see.

262
00:18:00,034 --> 00:18:01,202
Does being a reporter

263
00:18:01,536 --> 00:18:03,746
give you the right to print
one's personal business

264
00:18:03,830 --> 00:18:05,540
and gossip about it in the open?

265
00:18:05,999 --> 00:18:07,000
What's with that glare?

266
00:18:07,542 --> 00:18:08,710
Do you want to punch me?

267
00:18:08,793 --> 00:18:10,336
She isn't someone

268
00:18:14,257 --> 00:18:16,467
the likes of you
can talk about so recklessly.

269
00:18:22,640 --> 00:18:23,850
Is this true love?

270
00:18:24,601 --> 00:18:26,436
She was with you for a long time.

271
00:18:30,982 --> 00:18:32,984
Did you punch me? Did you see that?

272
00:18:33,067 --> 00:18:34,402
- Yes.
- You saw that?

273
00:18:34,485 --> 00:18:35,820
Did you see him punch me first?

274
00:18:35,903 --> 00:18:37,614
- Yes.
- Have you lost your mind?

275
00:18:38,740 --> 00:18:39,741
Hey, you.

276
00:18:42,785 --> 00:18:45,413
So what if you're a reporter?

277
00:18:46,789 --> 00:18:47,832
- Oh, no.
- Stop him.

278
00:18:47,915 --> 00:18:49,167
- Get him off him.
- Gosh.

279
00:18:54,631 --> 00:18:57,091
BOO SE-YOUNG, HEAD OF HR

280
00:18:57,175 --> 00:18:59,093
What is this? Is this for real?

281
00:19:02,180 --> 00:19:04,307
HAEMU'S BROTHERLY STRIFE,
FEMME FATALE AUDITOR AT THE CENTER

282
00:19:05,558 --> 00:19:07,226
You're the one who told me

283
00:19:08,478 --> 00:19:11,064
to take a good look
at who's really falling apart.

284
00:19:12,815 --> 00:19:14,942
Who do you think that is?

285
00:19:15,985 --> 00:19:19,447
I don't think it's you or me

286
00:19:19,781 --> 00:19:21,699
or even Jeon Jae-yeol.

287
00:19:22,784 --> 00:19:26,120
Ki-jun seems to be
the one who's falling apart.

288
00:19:30,333 --> 00:19:31,459
What are you saying?

289
00:19:31,751 --> 00:19:35,171
Jeon Sung-yeol plans to stick
the foundation case on Ki-jun.

290
00:19:35,713 --> 00:19:39,300
He'll make it look like Jeon Jae-yeol
ordered your team to cover it up.

291
00:19:39,801 --> 00:19:41,135
That would be the cleanest outcome.

292
00:19:43,680 --> 00:19:45,139
I find that silly.

293
00:19:45,723 --> 00:19:48,434
How could Ki-jun and Jeon Jae-yeol
be accomplices?

294
00:19:50,311 --> 00:19:51,437
Hang on.

295
00:19:52,689 --> 00:19:53,815
Maybe they are accomplices

296
00:19:54,941 --> 00:19:57,485
in loving the same woman to death.

297
00:19:58,569 --> 00:19:59,654
Is that it?

298
00:20:03,700 --> 00:20:04,909
You don't seem to get it.

299
00:20:05,618 --> 00:20:07,245
The word "accomplice"

300
00:20:07,829 --> 00:20:10,206
refers to you and Jeon Sung-yeol.

301
00:20:11,249 --> 00:20:13,209
You frame people
by twisting facts and exaggerating

302
00:20:13,292 --> 00:20:14,752
to turn someone into a scapegoat.

303
00:20:16,254 --> 00:20:18,005
People who conspire to do such things

304
00:20:19,424 --> 00:20:21,092
are called accomplices.

305
00:20:22,510 --> 00:20:24,345
All you did by siding
with Jeon Sung-yeol

306
00:20:24,887 --> 00:20:28,015
was bring down the friend
who helped you when you were in need.

307
00:20:29,976 --> 00:20:31,436
Was that your plan, too?

308
00:20:33,938 --> 00:20:35,773
Not only did you ruin
Jeon Jae-yeol's life

309
00:20:36,441 --> 00:20:39,444
but you're the type who brings
trouble to people around you.

310
00:20:40,695 --> 00:20:42,822
Do you even know Ki-jun
is at the police station?

311
00:20:43,823 --> 00:20:46,534
He assaulted the journalist
who exposed you.

312
00:20:53,416 --> 00:20:54,542
Settle?

313
00:20:54,625 --> 00:20:58,004
I have no intention of settling.
That's final.

314
00:20:58,296 --> 00:21:01,382
Check the CCTV and witnesses
and see who punched whom first.

315
00:21:01,466 --> 00:21:04,010
He attacked me,
and I was only defending myself.

316
00:21:04,427 --> 00:21:06,179
Sure. Whatever.

317
00:21:06,262 --> 00:21:07,972
I won't settle, either.

318
00:21:08,139 --> 00:21:13,060
Oh, and I'll sue this guy here
for defamation.

319
00:21:13,144 --> 00:21:16,147
He brought up someone's personal life
that's unrelated to the case

320
00:21:16,230 --> 00:21:18,024
to write a malicious piece.

321
00:21:18,107 --> 00:21:21,194
"Malicious"?
How dare you call it that?

322
00:21:21,486 --> 00:21:25,823
Using personal details
to paint a nice story is what I do!

323
00:21:25,907 --> 00:21:28,910
- It's in the public interest!
- "Public interest"?

324
00:21:30,244 --> 00:21:32,121
How is that public interest?

325
00:21:33,790 --> 00:21:39,045
She's not someone you can define
with a few lines of journalism.

326
00:21:39,128 --> 00:21:42,882
The kind of life she had,
how she fought to survive

327
00:21:43,299 --> 00:21:46,552
what choices she had made,
and how those choices tormented her

328
00:21:47,470 --> 00:21:49,555
were all taken out of context.

329
00:21:51,307 --> 00:21:55,353
You made a spectacle of her wounds,
and you call that...

330
00:21:56,813 --> 00:21:59,816
What kind of public interest is that?

331
00:22:02,235 --> 00:22:03,402
Goodness.

332
00:22:04,445 --> 00:22:05,822
You must like her a lot.

333
00:22:08,157 --> 00:22:10,159
Yes, I like her a lot.

334
00:22:10,576 --> 00:22:12,245
Because she's a good person.

335
00:22:13,454 --> 00:22:15,832
You can scorn and mock all you want

336
00:22:17,083 --> 00:22:19,043
but you'll never hurt her.

337
00:22:20,545 --> 00:22:23,005
I know who she truly is

338
00:22:24,507 --> 00:22:26,259
and I'll protect her until the end.

339
00:22:30,888 --> 00:22:32,139
I'm not making any settlements.

340
00:22:52,702 --> 00:22:53,870
Ms. Joo?

341
00:22:56,205 --> 00:22:57,290
What the...

342
00:22:57,498 --> 00:22:58,666
You startled me.

343
00:23:00,543 --> 00:23:01,752
Have some tofu.

344
00:23:08,050 --> 00:23:10,386
- Does it hurt?
- Yes, be gentle.

345
00:23:13,890 --> 00:23:15,349
Don't be a drama queen.

346
00:23:16,058 --> 00:23:19,645
I have thin and soft skin.
That's why.

347
00:23:19,729 --> 00:23:21,355
If you're that frail and soft

348
00:23:21,606 --> 00:23:23,149
why would you go around
punching people?

349
00:23:23,232 --> 00:23:26,235
Do you think you're a kid?
Why would you get into a fight?

350
00:23:32,199 --> 00:23:33,367
You did well.

351
00:23:33,951 --> 00:23:35,328
I felt great.

352
00:23:35,411 --> 00:23:37,580
I should've been the one
to teach him a lesson.

353
00:23:39,040 --> 00:23:42,877
Reporter Park was really lucky.

354
00:23:43,252 --> 00:23:46,172
He should be glad
I'm the one who beat him up.

355
00:23:48,090 --> 00:23:50,301
Take a pill to make sure
this doesn't fester before bed.

356
00:23:50,551 --> 00:23:51,969
- Okay?
- What?

357
00:23:53,763 --> 00:23:54,805
Wait.

358
00:23:56,140 --> 00:23:57,141
Hey.

359
00:24:00,436 --> 00:24:01,437
Are you leaving?

360
00:24:02,521 --> 00:24:04,106
I should. I have my own place.

361
00:24:04,482 --> 00:24:05,858
It's really cold out.

362
00:24:05,942 --> 00:24:08,069
I drove here.
I'll put the heater on full blast.

363
00:24:08,152 --> 00:24:10,237
It's late. You might
doze off at the wheel.

364
00:24:10,321 --> 00:24:11,489
I'm perfectly fine.

365
00:24:11,572 --> 00:24:13,532
Don't you worry and sleep well.

366
00:24:13,616 --> 00:24:14,617
See you.

367
00:24:16,535 --> 00:24:18,037
I have a tree.

368
00:24:21,040 --> 00:24:23,793
Shall we decorate my Christmas tree?

369
00:24:26,087 --> 00:24:28,631
You have a Christmas tree at home?

370
00:24:46,857 --> 00:24:48,859
Wow, it's beautiful.

371
00:24:55,741 --> 00:24:56,993
You know

372
00:24:57,493 --> 00:24:59,078
this is the first time
I've put up a Christmas tree.

373
00:24:59,537 --> 00:25:00,579
Really?

374
00:25:00,788 --> 00:25:03,624
- Didn't you have one at home?
- No.

375
00:25:04,375 --> 00:25:07,169
I had no room for anything sparkly.

376
00:25:11,507 --> 00:25:12,550
From now on

377
00:25:13,259 --> 00:25:14,635
we'll do this together every year.

378
00:25:16,595 --> 00:25:20,224
We should hang gems next year
like gold and silver trinkets.

379
00:25:20,850 --> 00:25:21,892
Gold is too expensive now.

380
00:25:22,268 --> 00:25:25,980
I even got a star for you.
Getting gold will be a piece of cake.

381
00:25:27,773 --> 00:25:30,735
You're right.
I also prefer gold to a star.

382
00:25:31,902 --> 00:25:32,945
I knew it.

383
00:25:37,575 --> 00:25:38,784
It's so pretty.

384
00:25:56,886 --> 00:25:57,887
INCOMING CALL

385
00:25:59,847 --> 00:26:01,223
Hello, Joo In-a speaking.

386
00:26:01,766 --> 00:26:04,477
Hello, I'm Ki-jun's big sister.

387
00:26:09,648 --> 00:26:12,193
New articles and comments
keep coming up

388
00:26:12,985 --> 00:26:15,196
but Ki-jun won't take
any of our calls.

389
00:26:16,697 --> 00:26:19,325
Even if we were to get through
and ask about it

390
00:26:19,742 --> 00:26:22,453
I don't think he'd tell us anything.

391
00:26:23,537 --> 00:26:24,914
We tried...

392
00:26:27,333 --> 00:26:29,752
We couldn't take it. So here we are.

393
00:26:30,753 --> 00:26:31,879
I see.

394
00:26:32,421 --> 00:26:33,756
What kind of person

395
00:26:34,507 --> 00:26:35,841
are you really?

396
00:26:37,426 --> 00:26:38,761
- Pardon?
- Well...

397
00:26:39,136 --> 00:26:42,181
You nursed our Ki-jun back to health

398
00:26:42,473 --> 00:26:45,684
so we assumed you two
had feelings for each other.

399
00:26:47,520 --> 00:26:51,649
There's talk that you're
the VP's mistress or something...

400
00:26:52,149 --> 00:26:53,234
The heck...

401
00:26:54,819 --> 00:26:56,946
We're not here to start a fight.

402
00:26:57,905 --> 00:27:01,575
As Ki-jun's family,
we want to know the facts.

403
00:27:03,285 --> 00:27:06,539
Our mom took to her bed because
she couldn't handle the shock.

404
00:27:06,914 --> 00:27:10,835
- We didn't know what to tell her.
- Ms. Joo.

405
00:27:11,335 --> 00:27:13,504
What happens to Ki-jun now?

406
00:27:14,380 --> 00:27:16,006
From what we read online

407
00:27:16,090 --> 00:27:18,592
he punched the journalist
who wrote about you.

408
00:27:18,676 --> 00:27:19,885
Is that true?

409
00:27:19,969 --> 00:27:21,554
Our Ki-jun

410
00:27:21,637 --> 00:27:25,683
never got into a fight growing up.

411
00:27:25,891 --> 00:27:28,519
Why would he suddenly...
My heart might explode.

412
00:27:28,602 --> 00:27:32,314
Is something
actually going on at work?

413
00:27:32,606 --> 00:27:36,485
Will Ki-jun
get penalized or something?

414
00:27:38,404 --> 00:27:39,655
Ms. Joo?

415
00:27:40,447 --> 00:27:42,825
You're Ki-jun's superior as well.

416
00:27:43,325 --> 00:27:44,994
Is there something

417
00:27:45,786 --> 00:27:49,915
you could do to help him?

418
00:28:05,222 --> 00:28:08,267
Hand in your company ID
while the investigation's ongoing.

419
00:28:28,078 --> 00:28:29,246
Hey, Ki-jun.

420
00:28:29,872 --> 00:28:30,998
Have you heard?

421
00:28:31,415 --> 00:28:32,917
So I'm going upstairs
to be interviewed.

422
00:28:33,000 --> 00:28:34,460
I called in case you got worried.

423
00:28:35,377 --> 00:28:36,378
Okay.

424
00:28:37,296 --> 00:28:39,256
I'm fine, so don't worry.

425
00:28:40,174 --> 00:28:42,301
Let's get something nice to eat
after I'm done.

426
00:28:43,219 --> 00:28:46,222
Sure. We can do that.
What do you want to eat?

427
00:28:48,390 --> 00:28:49,516
A toasted sandwich?

428
00:28:50,142 --> 00:28:53,020
Let's eat
that toasted sandwich again.

429
00:28:55,397 --> 00:28:57,066
You're eating that all the time.

430
00:29:00,778 --> 00:29:01,779
Ki-jun.

431
00:29:03,405 --> 00:29:04,406
Yes?

432
00:29:05,866 --> 00:29:08,035
No matter what I say from now on

433
00:29:08,577 --> 00:29:10,412
it means that I love you.

434
00:29:13,791 --> 00:29:15,000
My heart skipped a beat.

435
00:29:15,876 --> 00:29:16,877
I know you love me.

436
00:29:17,878 --> 00:29:18,921
I love you, too.

437
00:29:19,546 --> 00:29:21,465
So don't ever feel hurt.

438
00:29:45,406 --> 00:29:47,574
Ms. Joo, what brings you to...

439
00:29:51,787 --> 00:29:53,163
- What's this?
- What's going on?

440
00:29:56,083 --> 00:29:57,251
- Did she lock the door?
- What?

441
00:29:57,835 --> 00:29:59,086
- What's this?
- What's up with her?

442
00:30:00,546 --> 00:30:02,089
- What's this about?
- Joo In-a?

443
00:30:06,302 --> 00:30:07,511
Hello.

444
00:30:08,554 --> 00:30:10,848
I'm Joo In-a,
Haemu Group's Head of Audit.

445
00:30:10,931 --> 00:30:14,476
I'm here to explain where I stand
regarding the many suspicions.

446
00:30:17,187 --> 00:30:19,815
Will you make a statement
about yesterday's article?

447
00:30:19,898 --> 00:30:22,109
Is it true
that you're dating your subordinate?

448
00:30:22,192 --> 00:30:24,403
Did you really cover up
the VP's corruption?

449
00:30:25,237 --> 00:30:28,407
It's not true that a certain employee
covered up the corruption.

450
00:30:28,949 --> 00:30:33,662
Mr. Noh actually raised concerns
about the matter under suspicion.

451
00:30:33,912 --> 00:30:36,081
Why was there no investigation?

452
00:30:40,377 --> 00:30:42,004
I put a stop to it.

453
00:30:45,049 --> 00:30:46,675
I abused my authority.

454
00:30:47,301 --> 00:30:50,637
I told the employee
not to do anything.

455
00:30:52,765 --> 00:30:54,433
He was just being used

456
00:30:54,933 --> 00:30:55,934
by me.

457
00:30:56,268 --> 00:30:57,853
Why did you give such an instruction?

458
00:30:57,936 --> 00:31:01,190
Why did you use your subordinate
to cover up a case?

459
00:31:03,192 --> 00:31:05,569
I did so to protect VP Jeon Jae-yeol.

460
00:31:08,280 --> 00:31:12,117
My personal feelings clouded
my judgment as Head of Audit.

461
00:31:12,743 --> 00:31:15,788
I will take
full responsibility for it.

462
00:31:15,871 --> 00:31:16,872
I apologize.

463
00:31:16,955 --> 00:31:19,083
What do you mean
by "personal feelings"?

464
00:31:19,208 --> 00:31:21,835
Are you admitting
to your affair with the VP?

465
00:31:35,349 --> 00:31:37,935
3 MONTHS LATER

466
00:32:20,936 --> 00:32:22,062
FORWARDER: SAEMUN INTERNATIONAL

467
00:32:22,146 --> 00:32:24,022
VOLUME ERROR

468
00:32:31,947 --> 00:32:35,159
Look at her
staring fiercely at everything.

469
00:32:35,451 --> 00:32:36,910
That's why people call her
the human scanner.

470
00:32:37,453 --> 00:32:38,912
You can tell
that she was in the Audit Team.

471
00:32:39,163 --> 00:32:41,832
Did you see her picking out a fault
with a shipment to Europe last week?

472
00:32:42,124 --> 00:32:44,543
So people who are good at their job
are good no matter where they are.

473
00:32:44,626 --> 00:32:46,086
She surely is competent.

474
00:32:46,170 --> 00:32:48,130
That must be why
the vice president fell for her.

475
00:33:01,560 --> 00:33:03,228
That was the seventh time today.

476
00:33:03,312 --> 00:33:04,480
DIMENSION RECOGNITION ERROR

477
00:33:05,147 --> 00:33:06,648
It's definitely on the rise.

478
00:33:10,819 --> 00:33:15,699
MARCH 3RD, 2026
7 DIMENSION RECOGNITION ERRORS

479
00:33:27,127 --> 00:33:29,922
Your call cannot be connected.
You will be redirected to voicemail.

480
00:33:30,005 --> 00:33:32,216
After the beep,
you will be charged...

481
00:33:34,384 --> 00:33:38,680
EXCLUSIVE: THE PROSECUTION
FINDS JEON JAE-YEOL OF HAEMU

482
00:33:38,764 --> 00:33:43,519
FREE FROM ALL SUSPICION
INCLUDING PROFESSIONAL NEGLIGENCE

483
00:33:56,448 --> 00:33:58,158
Who told you
it was okay to go ahead with this?

484
00:33:59,159 --> 00:34:01,245
You need to file a planning report
before doing this.

485
00:34:02,037 --> 00:34:04,748
Audit Team Three handles matters
that come through reports

486
00:34:05,290 --> 00:34:07,000
so it is hard to file
a planning report each time.

487
00:34:07,084 --> 00:34:08,794
Who told you it had to be every time?

488
00:34:09,169 --> 00:34:11,421
This is Sales Team One
we're talking about.

489
00:34:11,588 --> 00:34:14,258
Don't you know that the head,
Mr. Cheon, is the immediate junior

490
00:34:14,341 --> 00:34:15,801
of VP Jeon Sung-yeol?

491
00:34:15,884 --> 00:34:18,053
I decided that an investigation
was necessary in the process

492
00:34:18,136 --> 00:34:20,639
of confirming the authenticity
of the report, and...

493
00:34:20,722 --> 00:34:23,267
And who are you to decide?

494
00:34:24,851 --> 00:34:26,562
- Leader of Team Three.
- Yes, sir.

495
00:34:26,937 --> 00:34:28,105
Come over here.

496
00:34:28,522 --> 00:34:30,148
- Right now?
- Yes.

497
00:34:31,483 --> 00:34:32,568
Yes, sure.

498
00:34:35,737 --> 00:34:38,574
Goodness. I never thought

499
00:34:39,074 --> 00:34:42,244
I'd stick around doing this job
long enough to miss Ms. Joo.

500
00:34:42,327 --> 00:34:43,495
Tell me about it.

501
00:34:44,037 --> 00:34:47,332
Ms. Joo also yelled at us,
but everything she said was right.

502
00:34:47,416 --> 00:34:51,378
But now, everything in the Audit Team
has become political.

503
00:34:51,920 --> 00:34:53,672
I hear it's all the same
in other departments, too.

504
00:34:53,755 --> 00:34:56,967
The entire business
is under Jeon Sung-yeol's reign.

505
00:34:57,050 --> 00:34:59,303
Good grief.
What is happening to this company?

506
00:34:59,845 --> 00:35:01,430
Good work, Mr. Noh.

507
00:35:01,513 --> 00:35:03,473
You must be feeling down,
so why don't we grab a drink?

508
00:35:03,724 --> 00:35:05,434
- He's not here.
- What?

509
00:35:06,059 --> 00:35:09,521
He ran out
as soon as the clock hit six o'clock.

510
00:35:09,896 --> 00:35:10,939
Again?

511
00:35:11,023 --> 00:35:13,025
Where has he been going
in such a hurry lately?

512
00:35:13,358 --> 00:35:17,029
Let him be. He wouldn't want to be
in the office even for a second.

513
00:35:17,112 --> 00:35:20,198
People still gossip about Ms. Joo,
both online and offline.

514
00:35:21,408 --> 00:35:23,118
It's a wonder
that he didn't quit his job.

515
00:35:23,201 --> 00:35:25,954
Ms. Joo was really cruel back then.

516
00:35:26,038 --> 00:35:29,333
How could she say she only used him
in front of everyone?

517
00:35:29,750 --> 00:35:32,753
Gosh. I hope
he comes around soon enough.

518
00:35:36,340 --> 00:35:38,091
Why don't we set him up
on a blind date?

519
00:35:38,175 --> 00:35:39,468
- Yes.
- That sounds nice.

520
00:35:39,551 --> 00:35:40,761
What do you say, Ms. Yoon?

521
00:35:40,844 --> 00:35:42,554
Is there anyone you know?

522
00:35:43,096 --> 00:35:44,222
He's right.

523
00:35:46,350 --> 00:35:47,726
I don't have friends.

524
00:35:48,644 --> 00:35:49,770
What about any older girls?

525
00:35:50,354 --> 00:35:52,564
It'd be weird
if she were younger than you.

526
00:35:53,065 --> 00:35:54,358
- Think about it.
- Anyone, Ms. Pyun?

527
00:35:54,441 --> 00:35:55,442
No.

528
00:36:05,744 --> 00:36:07,412
I just got on the Olympic Expressway.

529
00:36:07,496 --> 00:36:09,748
I'll be right on the highway
after getting into the interchange.

530
00:36:09,998 --> 00:36:11,958
Okay, I'm already
on the Gyeongbu Expressway

531
00:36:12,042 --> 00:36:13,794
and heading to Seoul.

532
00:36:14,836 --> 00:36:16,797
I'll get off the ramp soon, too

533
00:36:16,880 --> 00:36:18,256
so let's meet at Giheung today.

534
00:36:18,632 --> 00:36:20,759
I'll be at the Mannamui Gwangjang
Service Area in five minutes.

535
00:36:20,842 --> 00:36:22,469
Just give up.

536
00:36:23,387 --> 00:36:24,513
Come on.

537
00:36:25,097 --> 00:36:26,765
I left really early today.

538
00:36:28,892 --> 00:36:35,607
MANNAMUI GWANGJANG SERVICE AREA

539
00:36:42,197 --> 00:36:44,741
Come on. Why do you always
drive so far to come here?

540
00:36:44,825 --> 00:36:46,368
I said I'd come over.

541
00:36:46,993 --> 00:36:48,662
Can't you wait a little
in front of the center?

542
00:36:49,788 --> 00:36:51,873
Or we could meet
at a service area nearer to you.

543
00:36:51,957 --> 00:36:54,543
By then, the northbound expressway
will have less traffic.

544
00:36:55,460 --> 00:36:56,712
Work must be tough enough for you.

545
00:36:56,795 --> 00:36:59,297
I told you not to drive
so far from there.

546
00:37:01,508 --> 00:37:04,720
Anyway, since I lost again,
the snacks are on me.

547
00:37:06,012 --> 00:37:08,265
Then why don't we buy
some sausage and rice cake skewers

548
00:37:09,057 --> 00:37:10,600
and get some rest over there?

549
00:37:14,730 --> 00:37:15,731
What?

550
00:37:16,189 --> 00:37:17,899
Why would you eat skewers over there?

551
00:37:21,027 --> 00:37:22,112
Let's go.

552
00:37:44,468 --> 00:37:46,595
You know what?
I'm seriously starting to get mad.

553
00:37:47,012 --> 00:37:48,513
These files are all confidential

554
00:37:48,597 --> 00:37:50,515
so I couldn't lay them out
in the service area.

555
00:37:51,057 --> 00:37:52,267
In that case

556
00:37:52,601 --> 00:37:55,437
you could've just flatly said
we were coming here to work.

557
00:37:55,604 --> 00:37:57,397
Did you have to give
a flirtatious look and say

558
00:37:59,065 --> 00:38:00,984
"Should we go there?"

559
00:38:01,067 --> 00:38:03,570
My eyes have always been
rather flirtatious.

560
00:38:06,907 --> 00:38:09,868
Gosh, you always need
to do things your way.

561
00:38:09,951 --> 00:38:13,830
Right? You did this when you lied
before the cameras that you used me.

562
00:38:13,914 --> 00:38:15,624
He was just being used.

563
00:38:15,707 --> 00:38:18,168
You also did that when you decided
to move to the logistics center

564
00:38:18,251 --> 00:38:19,586
without telling me.

565
00:38:22,130 --> 00:38:24,591
In-a, just hand in your resignation.

566
00:38:25,050 --> 00:38:27,469
You'll get a disciplinary hearing
and be exiled to some far-off post.

567
00:38:27,969 --> 00:38:29,930
Every step of it will be

568
00:38:30,639 --> 00:38:32,808
devastating and humiliating
to endure.

569
00:38:32,891 --> 00:38:33,934
No.

570
00:38:34,309 --> 00:38:36,228
I will face my consequences
and be disciplined

571
00:38:36,311 --> 00:38:38,021
to take responsibility
for everything I have done.

572
00:38:40,357 --> 00:38:43,026
But I do have one favor
to ask of you, Se-young.

573
00:38:44,653 --> 00:38:46,071
Can you appoint me

574
00:38:46,822 --> 00:38:48,073
to the logistics center?

575
00:38:48,532 --> 00:38:51,201
Joo In-a always has a plan.

576
00:38:51,284 --> 00:38:52,702
It's a plan of her own.

577
00:38:52,994 --> 00:38:54,579
And I'm simply a part of her plan.

578
00:38:56,039 --> 00:38:57,499
Don't say it like that.

579
00:38:58,083 --> 00:38:59,125
A part of my plan?

580
00:38:59,835 --> 00:39:00,877
You are...

581
00:39:05,340 --> 00:39:06,424
a variable.

582
00:39:07,008 --> 00:39:09,344
You're a completely
unexpected lucky variable

583
00:39:09,594 --> 00:39:12,097
which I had never planned for
or even saw coming.

584
00:39:14,266 --> 00:39:15,600
At least you know
how to talk smoothly.

585
00:39:32,784 --> 00:39:34,953
- Was that your father?
- I think the issue with the machine

586
00:39:35,036 --> 00:39:36,329
is due to a defective part.

587
00:39:37,247 --> 00:39:38,915
Are you not going to pick up
his calls now?

588
00:39:42,711 --> 00:39:43,712
Think about it.

589
00:39:44,170 --> 00:39:47,757
From what I overheard last time,
he just wanted a meal with you.

590
00:39:58,768 --> 00:40:00,395
Are you listening?

591
00:40:01,313 --> 00:40:03,189
And why do you keep

592
00:40:03,273 --> 00:40:05,609
picking out the sausages
and giving me the rice cake pieces?

593
00:40:05,692 --> 00:40:09,070
Then there's no point in eating
the sausage and rice cake skewer.

594
00:40:09,571 --> 00:40:11,740
- But I guess it's good.
- That's it!

595
00:40:12,741 --> 00:40:14,200
That might be Jeon Sung-yeol's plan.

596
00:40:15,785 --> 00:40:18,371
He's picking out just the sausages
and keeping only what's good

597
00:40:18,914 --> 00:40:20,582
to throw away the rest.

598
00:40:29,215 --> 00:40:31,509
Let's liquidate five subsidiaries
that are suffering

599
00:40:31,593 --> 00:40:33,178
from structural chronic losses
within this year.

600
00:40:35,013 --> 00:40:36,097
Mr. Vice President.

601
00:40:36,181 --> 00:40:39,434
These subsidiaries
employ a large number of people.

602
00:40:39,517 --> 00:40:42,896
This liquidation will leave
tens of thousands of people jobless.

603
00:40:42,979 --> 00:40:44,022
Mr. Ko.

604
00:40:44,356 --> 00:40:45,732
A business isn't the soup kitchen.

605
00:40:45,815 --> 00:40:47,943
We can't feed those
who don't bring in profit.

606
00:40:49,569 --> 00:40:50,654
Also, Ms. Boo.

607
00:40:51,321 --> 00:40:53,323
What's taking you so long
with the personnel reduction?

608
00:40:53,615 --> 00:40:56,201
Well, there are procedures
I must abide by to do that...

609
00:40:56,284 --> 00:40:58,203
If I were going
to stick to procedures

610
00:40:58,286 --> 00:40:59,996
what do I need you for?

611
00:41:00,956 --> 00:41:02,916
Can you come up with something
more creative?

612
00:41:02,999 --> 00:41:04,709
If we do not abide
by the necessary procedures

613
00:41:04,793 --> 00:41:06,836
it will cause many legal
and management risks...

614
00:41:06,920 --> 00:41:08,088
Exactly.

615
00:41:08,546 --> 00:41:10,674
Isn't the whole point
of paying you good money

616
00:41:10,757 --> 00:41:13,343
to have you manage those risks?

617
00:41:17,389 --> 00:41:18,515
Everyone.

618
00:41:18,598 --> 00:41:19,891
Some tens of thousands
of jobless people

619
00:41:19,975 --> 00:41:22,060
are just a speck of margin of error
in the financial statement.

620
00:41:22,769 --> 00:41:24,312
Stop playing it safe

621
00:41:24,771 --> 00:41:26,231
and earn your keep.

622
00:41:27,565 --> 00:41:28,566
Got it?

623
00:41:32,988 --> 00:41:35,532
Once you sign this paper,
it'll finalize the divorce agreement.

624
00:41:40,078 --> 00:41:42,372
HUSBAND: JEON JAE-YEOL

625
00:42:05,395 --> 00:42:08,857
WIFE

626
00:42:19,576 --> 00:42:20,660
Hyun-young...

627
00:42:25,665 --> 00:42:26,750
Hyun-young.

628
00:42:34,591 --> 00:42:36,384
It's not too late.

629
00:42:36,885 --> 00:42:39,262
You were found innocent
or not guilty or whatever.

630
00:42:40,221 --> 00:42:42,098
That means you aren't guilty.

631
00:42:43,224 --> 00:42:46,394
If you divorce me right now,
you'll literally end up penniless.

632
00:42:47,145 --> 00:42:48,396
Look at your father's condition

633
00:42:48,480 --> 00:42:50,148
and how the company
is in Sung-yeol's hands.

634
00:42:52,859 --> 00:42:54,235
I said I'd help.

635
00:42:55,570 --> 00:42:58,073
I said I'd be your lifeline.
What's wrong with you?

636
00:43:05,205 --> 00:43:06,206
Is it Joo In-a?

637
00:43:08,249 --> 00:43:09,709
It's because of her, right?

638
00:43:11,377 --> 00:43:12,670
It's not that.

639
00:43:13,755 --> 00:43:14,756
You and I

640
00:43:15,840 --> 00:43:17,801
just can't be happy with each other.

641
00:43:17,884 --> 00:43:19,427
What the heck do you know
about my happiness?

642
00:43:22,305 --> 00:43:23,723
I know that I can't give it to you.

643
00:43:25,058 --> 00:43:27,227
So I really want you to find it.

644
00:43:28,603 --> 00:43:30,396
Because I plan to start looking, too.

645
00:43:33,483 --> 00:43:34,609
Jerk.

646
00:44:06,182 --> 00:44:08,351
Line A is stuck again.
Grab the technicians now!

647
00:44:09,060 --> 00:44:10,687
There's not much time left
before shipping.

648
00:44:11,020 --> 00:44:13,231
Darn it. Is it down again?
I can't keep working like this.

649
00:44:14,149 --> 00:44:15,984
This is getting worse and worse.

650
00:44:16,359 --> 00:44:17,569
How was it before?

651
00:44:17,652 --> 00:44:19,279
It wasn't this bad.

652
00:44:19,362 --> 00:44:22,365
After the vice president changed,
the parts supplier also changed.

653
00:44:22,448 --> 00:44:23,616
It's been like this since then.

654
00:44:24,367 --> 00:44:25,451
Where does the shipment

655
00:44:26,327 --> 00:44:27,537
for those parts come into?

656
00:45:47,784 --> 00:45:48,993
Are you okay?

657
00:45:50,954 --> 00:45:54,082
I know it was somewhere here.

658
00:45:54,791 --> 00:45:56,084
Are you looking for something?

659
00:45:56,668 --> 00:45:58,544
No, I thought I dropped something

660
00:45:58,753 --> 00:46:00,004
but I must've been wrong.

661
00:46:00,338 --> 00:46:01,422
Excuse me.

662
00:46:35,248 --> 00:46:36,374
You have reached Moo Kwang-il.

663
00:46:37,166 --> 00:46:38,960
Yes, I understand.
I'll be upstairs soon.

664
00:46:43,506 --> 00:46:44,716
You have reached Cha Sung-tae.

665
00:46:45,883 --> 00:46:47,969
Yes, all right. I'll be upstairs.

666
00:46:51,306 --> 00:46:52,765
This is Baek Hyun-kyu
of Audit Team Three.

667
00:46:53,308 --> 00:46:54,600
Yes, all right.

668
00:46:59,314 --> 00:47:01,607
What were the calls? What's going on?

669
00:47:05,069 --> 00:47:06,946
PERSONNEL RECORD
MOO KWANG-IL

670
00:47:07,030 --> 00:47:09,657
PERSONNEL RECORD
CHA SUNG-TAE

671
00:47:13,411 --> 00:47:15,204
Look at all these people.

672
00:47:16,622 --> 00:47:18,374
What are they all going to do?

673
00:47:19,751 --> 00:47:20,752
Goodness.

674
00:47:26,257 --> 00:47:27,383
Hello, Ms. Boo.

675
00:47:27,800 --> 00:47:29,635
- Have a seat, Mr. Moo.
- Sure.

676
00:47:58,122 --> 00:47:59,707
So our company

677
00:48:00,750 --> 00:48:03,252
is conducting a huge restructuring
and reorganization.

678
00:48:04,087 --> 00:48:05,213
From the Audit Team

679
00:48:06,047 --> 00:48:07,590
they plan to remove
Team Three entirely.

680
00:48:09,425 --> 00:48:10,551
What about us three?

681
00:48:11,177 --> 00:48:14,263
You three will probably get
transferred to another team.

682
00:48:21,813 --> 00:48:24,524
But Mr. Moo, Mr. Cha, and Hyun-kyu...

683
00:48:25,983 --> 00:48:27,151
probably won't...

684
00:48:29,695 --> 00:48:32,365
She'll ask them to retire voluntarily
within a certain period.

685
00:48:33,074 --> 00:48:34,242
If they don't leave in that time

686
00:48:34,325 --> 00:48:36,035
she'll pressure them
by cutting their severance pay.

687
00:48:37,203 --> 00:48:39,956
- That's right.
- This is insane.

688
00:48:43,418 --> 00:48:44,919
What are they going to do?

689
00:48:48,506 --> 00:48:49,590
You see...

690
00:48:53,094 --> 00:48:54,804
As I'd expected,
it was the problem with the parts.

691
00:48:55,138 --> 00:48:56,639
Only the packaging is brand new

692
00:48:56,722 --> 00:48:58,433
and what's inside is all beat-up.

693
00:48:59,058 --> 00:49:01,686
There's no way these new machines
would work smoothly with those.

694
00:49:01,769 --> 00:49:04,272
That would cause a problem
with the logistics process

695
00:49:04,355 --> 00:49:07,108
and the subsidiary, HM Trans,
will drop in its value.

696
00:49:07,191 --> 00:49:08,443
He probably plans to dispose of it.

697
00:49:08,901 --> 00:49:10,820
And the money he gets will be used
to secure his shares.

698
00:49:10,903 --> 00:49:12,864
The headquarters
is slowly downsizing, too.

699
00:49:13,364 --> 00:49:14,991
The restructuring began

700
00:49:16,325 --> 00:49:18,035
and Audit Team Three
will be dissolved.

701
00:49:18,536 --> 00:49:20,746
What? Team Three?

702
00:49:21,998 --> 00:49:24,834
Mr. Moo, Mr. Cha, and even Hyun-kyu

703
00:49:24,917 --> 00:49:26,252
got asked to accept
voluntary retirement.

704
00:49:27,170 --> 00:49:28,421
I wanted to tell you

705
00:49:29,297 --> 00:49:30,506
that I can't come over today.

706
00:49:31,340 --> 00:49:33,176
I think I should be here
with my teammates.

707
00:49:35,636 --> 00:49:36,929
Yes, of course.

708
00:49:38,347 --> 00:49:41,309
Or would you like to come?

709
00:49:41,767 --> 00:49:42,935
They'd all be happy to see you.

710
00:49:44,437 --> 00:49:45,480
Should I do that?

711
00:49:57,325 --> 00:50:01,704
Jeon Sung-yeol has yet to secure
all the shares he needs.

712
00:50:01,996 --> 00:50:04,373
We don't know how it'll play out,
so let's see...

713
00:50:04,457 --> 00:50:05,458
Mr. Noh.

714
00:50:08,377 --> 00:50:11,130
Don't make it sound that easy
just because it's not your business.

715
00:50:12,089 --> 00:50:13,508
What do you mean, you don't know?

716
00:50:13,591 --> 00:50:15,843
We were already notified.

717
00:50:16,552 --> 00:50:17,553
Okay?

718
00:50:22,016 --> 00:50:25,019
Drink slowly.
You're drinking way too fast.

719
00:50:25,853 --> 00:50:26,896
Ms. Pyun.

720
00:50:27,939 --> 00:50:29,398
You must think I'm a joke, too.

721
00:50:29,899 --> 00:50:33,152
Are you going to be stingy
even on a day like this?

722
00:50:34,403 --> 00:50:35,988
- Are you?
- That's not what I mean.

723
00:50:36,739 --> 00:50:38,282
Man. Come on.

724
00:50:39,325 --> 00:50:42,537
- Let me have it. I'll cook the meat.
- It's okay.

725
00:50:42,870 --> 00:50:44,539
- Just let me have it.
- Ms. Yoon!

726
00:50:45,331 --> 00:50:48,042
Cooking meat isn't an easy job.

727
00:50:48,125 --> 00:50:50,670
Don't make it sound like it's easy!

728
00:50:54,173 --> 00:50:57,134
I'm such an incompetent team leader

729
00:50:57,969 --> 00:51:00,471
and I feel too ashamed
to face every one of you.

730
00:51:01,806 --> 00:51:05,685
If I only had a bit of power

731
00:51:06,686 --> 00:51:08,771
I could have stopped

732
00:51:09,355 --> 00:51:10,731
our entire team

733
00:51:11,232 --> 00:51:13,776
from disappearing.

734
00:51:14,193 --> 00:51:17,196
I'm so sorry. I apologize.

735
00:51:18,447 --> 00:51:19,574
Goodness.

736
00:51:20,074 --> 00:51:22,451
What am I going to do now? Gosh.

737
00:51:24,495 --> 00:51:26,455
Oh, goodness.

738
00:51:26,998 --> 00:51:29,125
Thank you for treating us to beef,
Hae-young.

739
00:51:29,917 --> 00:51:32,086
Eat up, and please stop crying.

740
00:51:32,712 --> 00:51:33,713
MS. JOO IN-A

741
00:51:33,796 --> 00:51:36,841
- Where are you?
- Da-yae, will you manage without me?

742
00:51:47,935 --> 00:51:49,520
The word "accomplice"

743
00:51:50,438 --> 00:51:53,149
refers to you and Jeon Sung-yeol.

744
00:52:05,036 --> 00:52:06,996
HAEMU GROUP DISPOSITION PLAN

745
00:52:07,079 --> 00:52:10,750
I'm meeting Mr. Kang of TH,
so book a room at a hostess bar.

746
00:52:10,958 --> 00:52:12,460
And bring in
the right number of partners.

747
00:52:14,920 --> 00:52:18,549
Right. Yes, sir.

748
00:52:19,342 --> 00:52:20,343
What now?

749
00:52:20,885 --> 00:52:21,886
What's with that face?

750
00:52:23,429 --> 00:52:25,973
Wait, has Jae-yeol never asked you
to do something like this?

751
00:52:29,894 --> 00:52:31,312
You know it's just business.

752
00:52:32,021 --> 00:52:33,230
Handle it like a professional.

753
00:52:40,404 --> 00:52:41,530
I see.

754
00:52:42,114 --> 00:52:45,618
I get what you mean, Se-young.
Thank you. Bye.

755
00:52:48,663 --> 00:52:50,998
You said you were nearby,
but you never showed up.

756
00:52:52,333 --> 00:52:54,085
What was that serious call about?

757
00:52:54,168 --> 00:52:55,711
It's Ms. Boo of HR.

758
00:52:56,420 --> 00:52:59,131
I thought we should have someone
on our side at the headquarters

759
00:52:59,215 --> 00:53:01,384
so I compiled everything
I have gathered and sent it to her.

760
00:53:01,467 --> 00:53:03,260
Gosh, it's so cold.

761
00:53:03,761 --> 00:53:07,556
Goodness. It's cold,
so let's go inside and talk later.

762
00:53:07,640 --> 00:53:10,309
Why are you so lightly dressed?
Aren't you cold?

763
00:53:10,393 --> 00:53:12,687
You look colder than I.

764
00:53:13,521 --> 00:53:14,855
Your ears are so red.

765
00:53:15,106 --> 00:53:16,440
I can imagine that.

766
00:53:19,402 --> 00:53:20,653
Ms. Joo?

767
00:53:25,282 --> 00:53:26,409
Ms. Joo!

768
00:53:30,371 --> 00:53:31,497
I must be drunk out of my mind.

769
00:53:31,580 --> 00:53:33,290
Hey, that's our Mr. Noh!

770
00:53:33,374 --> 00:53:34,875
Where have you been?

771
00:53:35,126 --> 00:53:37,169
I've been looking for you.

772
00:53:37,878 --> 00:53:39,296
Is she your girlfriend?

773
00:53:39,839 --> 00:53:42,925
Hello, I'm Mr. Moo,
the incompetent team leader.

774
00:53:45,886 --> 00:53:49,265
Wow, you look just like
Ms. Joo In-a at our workplace.

775
00:53:49,348 --> 00:53:51,517
Hey, look.
She looks just like Ms. Joo!

776
00:53:57,565 --> 00:53:58,733
You're here.

777
00:54:02,403 --> 00:54:03,821
- Come here.
- Hey.

778
00:54:12,705 --> 00:54:15,583
Wait, so who asked whom out?

779
00:54:15,666 --> 00:54:17,084
- I did.
- I did.

780
00:54:17,501 --> 00:54:19,295
What? You two asked each other out?

781
00:54:19,378 --> 00:54:21,964
Look who's in love!

782
00:54:22,673 --> 00:54:26,844
So Ms. Joo's boyfriend
that you once mentioned

783
00:54:27,178 --> 00:54:28,554
was Mr. Noh?

784
00:54:29,305 --> 00:54:31,348
How did you know
who my boyfriend was?

785
00:54:31,432 --> 00:54:33,768
I could tell just by Mr. Noh's eyes.

786
00:54:36,437 --> 00:54:37,480
His eyes?

787
00:54:40,524 --> 00:54:43,277
Hey, Ms. Joo, wait a moment.

788
00:54:43,360 --> 00:54:46,697
What was the thing you said
during the interview?

789
00:54:46,781 --> 00:54:49,200
You said that
you were just using him.

790
00:54:50,201 --> 00:54:51,911
Isn't it obvious?

791
00:54:51,994 --> 00:54:57,583
You told a white lie
for Mr. Noh's sake, isn't that so?

792
00:54:57,666 --> 00:54:59,168
I knew you'd notice, Hae-young.

793
00:55:00,085 --> 00:55:01,921
She was such a romantic!

794
00:55:02,004 --> 00:55:04,673
You two look great together.
I mean it.

795
00:55:05,466 --> 00:55:07,384
You two must be
the best couple there is.

796
00:55:08,803 --> 00:55:09,970
- Are you crying?
- What's with him?

797
00:55:10,054 --> 00:55:11,430
- Why are you crying?
- Yes, why?

798
00:55:11,514 --> 00:55:12,973
- Thanks.
- Gosh.

799
00:55:13,057 --> 00:55:14,850
There's finally a couple
from our Audit Team!

800
00:55:14,934 --> 00:55:19,313
And they're the biggest couple
of this century!

801
00:55:22,566 --> 00:55:25,653
But of course,
I can no longer call it

802
00:55:26,111 --> 00:55:27,738
our Audit Team.

803
00:55:31,700 --> 00:55:33,619
Yes, I shouldn't be so excited

804
00:55:34,453 --> 00:55:35,996
about someone else's love life
right now.

805
00:55:37,581 --> 00:55:38,874
You're right.

806
00:55:47,383 --> 00:55:49,468
The game isn't over yet.

807
00:55:50,553 --> 00:55:52,012
I promised you, didn't I?

808
00:55:52,096 --> 00:55:53,931
That I will be your iron fortress.

809
00:55:54,431 --> 00:55:57,434
And I will keep my promise
until the very end.

810
00:56:00,896 --> 00:56:02,940
Stay strong. It's not over yet!

811
00:56:03,816 --> 00:56:05,943
Your iron fortress stands here!

812
00:56:08,863 --> 00:56:10,030
Thank you!

813
00:56:11,448 --> 00:56:12,741
She's right.

814
00:56:18,664 --> 00:56:22,126
So why did you talk so big
before resolving everything?

815
00:56:22,626 --> 00:56:23,961
I know.

816
00:56:24,378 --> 00:56:26,589
Why am I
so full of myself these days?

817
00:56:27,715 --> 00:56:28,966
I mean, Mr. Moo was

818
00:56:29,675 --> 00:56:32,303
looking at me like this,
so I couldn't just stay still.

819
00:56:34,805 --> 00:56:37,266
I'm glad you did that.
You just have to solve this matter.

820
00:56:37,975 --> 00:56:39,268
- That's right.
- Yes.

821
00:56:39,351 --> 00:56:40,644
I think I can find a way.

822
00:56:40,728 --> 00:56:41,812
Not only is Se-young against him

823
00:56:41,896 --> 00:56:44,356
but there are directors
who are against Jeon Sung-yeol.

824
00:56:45,107 --> 00:56:47,484
In order to convince them
to cast their votes

825
00:56:48,027 --> 00:56:49,987
we need to give them
an alternative to Jeon Sung-yeol.

826
00:56:50,487 --> 00:56:53,824
It has to be someone who has enough
power and trust to go against him

827
00:56:53,908 --> 00:56:57,745
and someone whom the directors
will trust and cast their votes on.

828
00:56:59,663 --> 00:57:01,081
There's only Mr. Jeon Jae-yeol.

829
00:57:02,333 --> 00:57:03,959
Yes, you're right.

830
00:57:04,168 --> 00:57:05,294
But then

831
00:57:05,711 --> 00:57:07,546
we're showing up unannounced.

832
00:57:07,838 --> 00:57:09,924
Do you really think he'll meet us?

833
00:57:17,056 --> 00:57:19,516
I love you.

834
00:57:23,145 --> 00:57:24,980
I love you.

835
00:57:37,993 --> 00:57:39,286
It's called monstera.

836
00:57:42,748 --> 00:57:46,293
Thanks to these holes in the leaves,
the wind can travel easily.

837
00:57:47,044 --> 00:57:49,254
These help them live a long time
without ripping.

838
00:57:51,090 --> 00:57:52,132
That means...

839
00:57:54,635 --> 00:57:55,761
the wounds

840
00:57:57,012 --> 00:57:59,056
are their way of survival.

841
00:58:35,259 --> 00:58:37,803
We're talking about 150,000 people.

842
00:58:38,470 --> 00:58:40,389
If Jeon Sung-yeol sells everything
according to his plan

843
00:58:40,472 --> 00:58:42,433
that's the number of people
who will lose their livelihood.

844
00:58:43,809 --> 00:58:45,561
We have to stop
the worst from happening.

845
00:58:46,770 --> 00:58:48,856
We aren't asking you
to return to the company.

846
00:58:48,939 --> 00:58:51,817
We're just asking you
to help us persuade the directors

847
00:58:52,067 --> 00:58:55,654
so that the board will approve
of Jeon Sung-yeol's dismissal.

848
00:58:58,657 --> 00:59:02,244
In-a, don't you think
you're asking for too much?

849
00:59:06,415 --> 00:59:08,625
You pretended like you were
siding with me in front of the world

850
00:59:09,418 --> 00:59:10,961
to protect your man.

851
00:59:11,754 --> 00:59:14,673
Then you suddenly show up
and ask me to save the company?

852
00:59:16,592 --> 00:59:18,177
I have found my peace.

853
00:59:18,761 --> 00:59:20,345
My mother has become
much better, too.

854
00:59:21,472 --> 00:59:23,223
Please don't get me involved
in this matter.

855
00:59:54,463 --> 00:59:55,672
Did you ask for me?

856
01:00:00,010 --> 01:00:01,261
What the heck?

857
01:00:01,637 --> 01:00:02,679
What did you do?

858
01:00:02,763 --> 01:00:05,307
Don't you know what it means
to get the right number of partners?

859
01:00:05,808 --> 01:00:07,226
I did what you asked me to do.

860
01:00:07,601 --> 01:00:10,521
I invited one employee
per participant to assist them.

861
01:00:10,604 --> 01:00:12,439
And they were all men!

862
01:00:14,399 --> 01:00:15,400
You...

863
01:00:16,068 --> 01:00:17,861
So you can think for yourself.

864
01:00:18,946 --> 01:00:22,366
I don't need anyone who thinks
and makes their own decision.

865
01:00:22,449 --> 01:00:24,243
All you need to do
is follow my decisions.

866
01:00:25,744 --> 01:00:26,829
Get out.

867
01:00:35,420 --> 01:00:36,588
Hey.

868
01:00:37,089 --> 01:00:38,715
Hasten the preparation
to sell HM Trans.

869
01:00:40,676 --> 01:00:43,011
I don't care. Just set the date!

870
01:00:50,269 --> 01:00:51,311
My dear son.

871
01:00:52,563 --> 01:00:53,730
Thank you.

872
01:00:55,107 --> 01:00:56,150
It's still hot.

873
01:01:17,171 --> 01:01:19,339
We're talking about 150,000 people.

874
01:01:20,132 --> 01:01:22,801
If Jeon Sung-yeol sells everything
according to his plan

875
01:01:22,885 --> 01:01:24,803
that's the number of people
who will lose their livelihood.

876
01:01:36,982 --> 01:01:38,192
SEARCH KEYWORD

877
01:01:41,445 --> 01:01:42,446
HAEMU GROUP

878
01:01:43,947 --> 01:01:45,824
RUMORS OF HAEMU SELLING HM TRANS

879
01:01:49,620 --> 01:01:52,581
HAEMU PLANS TO SELL HM TRANS

880
01:02:19,483 --> 01:02:20,525
Mr. Vice President!

881
01:02:20,609 --> 01:02:22,611
This is not a proper way
of selling a company.

882
01:02:22,694 --> 01:02:24,488
Withdraw the unfair dismissal!

883
01:02:24,571 --> 01:02:26,490
- Withdraw!
- Withdraw!

884
01:02:26,573 --> 01:02:28,242
Halt the hasty sell-off!

885
01:02:28,325 --> 01:02:30,160
- Halt!
- Halt!

886
01:02:34,164 --> 01:02:35,249
Everyone.

887
01:02:36,375 --> 01:02:41,129
What you're doing here is considered
obstruction of business. Got it?

888
01:02:41,213 --> 01:02:43,006
THIS IS NOT RESTRUCTURING, BUT FIRING

889
01:02:43,799 --> 01:02:46,260
Remove them before my guests arrive.

890
01:02:49,346 --> 01:02:51,098
- "Remove"?
- Remove us?

891
01:02:51,723 --> 01:02:52,975
What does he mean by that?

892
01:02:53,684 --> 01:02:55,602
- Hey, what are you doing?
- You can't do this!

893
01:03:01,316 --> 01:03:02,985
UNITED WE FIGHT

894
01:03:11,285 --> 01:03:12,911
Ms. Joo!

895
01:04:07,215 --> 01:04:10,135
FILING FOR LOVE

896
01:04:10,761 --> 01:04:13,430
GUEST APPEARANCE BY OH EUI-SHIK

897
01:04:38,413 --> 01:04:39,790
An emergency board meeting?

898
01:04:39,873 --> 01:04:41,375
Is he going to dismiss the CEO first?

899
01:04:41,458 --> 01:04:43,293
- Target found. I'm tailing him.
- Over there.

900
01:04:43,668 --> 01:04:46,213
Man, it was like
a scene from a movie.

901
01:04:46,546 --> 01:04:48,173
Wait, a marriage?

902
01:04:48,256 --> 01:04:50,008
No, I don't do marriages.

903
01:04:50,092 --> 01:04:51,218
It doubles the risk.

904
01:04:51,301 --> 01:04:53,428
Not even with me?
Why are you hesitating?

905
01:04:53,512 --> 01:04:55,806
It feels like they're starting
to swap personalities.

906
01:04:56,264 --> 01:04:58,558
They say you grow alike
with the one you love.

907
01:04:58,725 --> 01:04:59,768
Did you just laugh?

908
01:04:59,851 --> 01:05:02,646
Could there still be
something going on between them?

909
01:05:03,146 --> 01:05:04,523
I have something to say, Ki-ju.n

910
01:05:18,412 --> 01:05:20,414
Subtitles by Eunsook Youn
and Jennifer Lim

